    "claims": [
      {
        "id": "claim.repository_identity",
        "kind": "fact",
        "text": "IPTVnator is a cross-platform open-source IPTV player built with Electron and Angular, supporting M3U/M3U8 playlists, XMLTV EPG URLs, Xtream Codes, and Stalker portals; it explicitly does not provide playlists or other content.",
        "truth": "source_verified",
        "intent": "intended",
        "code_anchors": [
          {
            "file": "README.md"
          }
        ],
        "about": "component.repository"
      },
      {
        "id": "claim.workspace_commands",
        "kind": "fact",
        "text": "The documented local setup is Corepack plus pnpm install; main scripts serve Angular only with `pnpm run serve:frontend`, serve the Electron app with `pnpm run serve:backend`, build web/backend targets, run frontend/backend/unit tests, typecheck web/backend, and package or make Electron distributables through Nx targets.",
        "truth": "source_verified",
        "intent": "intended",
        "code_anchors": [
          {
            "file": "README.md"
          },
          {
            "file": "package.json"
          }
        ],
        "about": "flow.develop_build_test"
      },
      {
        "id": "claim.workspace_shape",
        "kind": "fact",
        "text": "This repository is an Nx workspace whose primary apps include `web`, `electron-backend`, `remote-control-web`, mock servers, and website, while shared functionality is split into libraries for services, M3U state, playlist UI/import, portal features, workspace dashboard, UI, interfaces, and database access.",
        "truth": "source_verified",
        "intent": "intended",
        "code_anchors": [
